This project ("ytlite-skip-silence") implements an algorithm for
detecting silent sections in audio playback by measuring loudness
according to ITU-R BS.1770-4 ("Algorithms to measure audio programme
loudness and true-peak audio level"), an open international standard
published by the International Telecommunication Union.

The algorithm was studied by reverse-engineering the Overcast podcast
app (© Marco Arment / Overcast Radio LLC) for the sole purpose of
interoperability — i.e. providing a similar user experience for users
of the YTLite YouTube tweak. No source code, compiled binary code,
resources, assets, strings, or artwork from Overcast are included in
this repository. Only the algorithm (an open international standard)
and the public struct field layout (recovered from the binary's
@encode metadata, which is not subject to copyright) were used.

"Smart Speed" and "Voice Boost" are product feature names associated
with Overcast. This project is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or
sponsored by Overcast, Marco Arment, or Overcast Radio LLC. All
trademarks belong to their respective owners.

YouTube is a trademark of Google LLC. This project is not affiliated
with or endorsed by Google LLC. Use of YouTube is governed by Google's
Terms of Service.
